African, Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) group of countries should be accorded increased access to the European market, President Uhuru Kenyatta said on Thursday. He said deals such as the Economic Partnership Agreements (EPAs) should recognise each country’s level of development so that no country felt disadvantaged. ALSO READ:

